cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.ET, cs.PF, cs.CE 

This paper deals with the problem of locating the sources of forced low-frequency oscillations in power systems, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of control systems (cs.SY), data science (cs.DS), and electrical engineering (cs.ET). The paper proposes a systematic method for source detection that involves modeling generators as effective admittance matrices, which is a technique that is commonly used in power flow analysis (cs.PF) and circuit analysis (cs.CE). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.ET, cs.PF, and cs.CE, in that order.
